< Review>
Food was good, but service was terrible. We had called in a reservation, but when we arrived they said they didn't have it. Saw it on a note next to their phone with all the details and called them out on it. They didn't care.

Waited 45 mins for a table, then nearly 30 mins for a starter salad. When questioned about the salad after about 20 mins, our server gave a snarky reply that they have to cook the chicken on the salad, so it's not a 15 minute salad. Mmkay. Another 15 mins or so for food to start coming in waves.

One of the dishes that was supposed to be vegetarian showed up with sausage or ground beef in it. When we meet the server know, she didn't apologize and say let me go fix that for you. Instead she argued that it shouldn't have meat in it (obviously it shouldn't based on the menu description). She did get it remade quickly, and it was good, but she really needs to work on her customer service skills.

It's really a shame that the service was so bad here. What should have been a great family get together, was turned into a frustrating experience. Again, we all enjoyed our food, but I definitely won't be back next time I'm in town.< /Review>

< Text>
The food was OK. However, this is the filthiest restaurant we have been in for a long time. 2 of the 4 plates on the table looked like they literally hadn't been washed. Ok, that happens. There was food in various spots all over the floor, and a crayon. The tables all looked like they were wiped with a dirty rag. We were there at 3:30 on Sat afternoon 7-12, and one of only three tables being served, so it's not like it was in the midst of a meal rush, and nobody had time to push a broom for 5 minutes. We kept waiting to see if a server would at least pick up the crayon so they would slip on it. Nope. Two people with a $50 before tip lunch tab-sorry, but I'd rather eat somewhere with a cleanliness standard. Back to Blue Ribbon Pizza in Encinitas now, for our pizza fix. Or Leucadia pizza. Wish people took pride in their establishments-we were hoping it would be good, but pretty disappointed.<//Text>

<user>110810851381755731600<//user><user_name>David Guettler<//user_name><Time>1424945568222<//Time>< Rate>
5<//Rate>
< Text>
My time spent inside "Crust" was less than 5 minutes. I simply picked up a pizza to go.  I inhaled the environment of "Crust" in those few minutes.

The 5 stars I gave was 95 percent for the pizza and 5 percent for my short experience inside and over the phone ordering.

If your a serious pizza lover that appreciates quality and taste, this place is top tier for you.  Traveling often for business I get around the US and can tell you "Crust" is in the top 10 percent. (Been to NY and Chicago, interesting enough, and never had time to get pizza)

I created my own pizza.
I had a 10" pizza with Artisan crust (regular), Wisconsin mozzarella cheese, Portobello mushrooms, black olives and onions. My total was 14.85 and that was for two people. No complaints, your getting quality.  First and final opinion is this place has great pizza.  The only local pizza equal is "Marco's" in Vista, CA.

I will come here again, and I live in San Marcos 6 miles away.

The environment inside made me think i was inside"Chipotle" with servers and a bar added. That is not saying a bad thing. I am just  describing the inside as best I can. Wide beer and wine selection.  I interacted with three employees and they were all friendly. Others will probably disagree, but I PERSONALLY would not go there with a group bigger than 6. Customer service over the phone for the order was great. Plenty of parking.

Pizzaholic tourists getting the "shakes" should definitely go here if in Carlsbad, CA.<//Text>

< user_name>
Randy Thomasian<//user_name>
<date>1531615088796< /date><rating>2<//rating>< review>
I have been living here for about 7 months or so. Here is my experience so far.
1. The laminated flooring was damaged prior to us moving in. There was a lot of indent marks on the floor from the previous Tennant's furniture. We had informed them of this and they stated they can not do anything for us but make sure its documented so we don't get charged upon move out. We will see if they try and charge us upon move out.
2. The fridge has had to get fixed twice. It emitted a very loud noise during the night on two separate incidents. It still makes sounds every so often that it doesn't bother us anymore.
3. The gate has been broken for over a few months now.
4. upon entering the apartment complex you will notice none of the lights on the garage ports are working until you curve right on the road. It is really dark in the entrance and that can be very dangerous. It has been like that for months as well.
6. My laundry was stolen after leaving it for couple hours. Some might say, why would you leave your laundry un attended? Well when its 110 degrees outside with no AC in that room and I have a chronic lung disease. I am not able to stay out that long in those terms.
7. Guest Parking is horrible. If you come home after 4, you will have no guest parking. The Tenants park in guest parking since the parking for guest are closer to their home. I stated this to management and nothing was done about it.
8. The trees are damaging the vehicles.
9. There has been an abandoned vehicle in front of my place longer than i have even been here. Many people have complained to the office that the vehicle needs to be towed. Since I moved in they have ticketed the car 4 times. I am sure there are living creatures in that car for how long its been sitting there as well. The car is still there and has not been towed.
10. A lady next door had a mother who was an alcoholic that came to my door late hours of the night asking to use my restroom since she was locked out of her daughters place. Another occasion she came to my door at midnight so I can call 911 for her. The police and ambulance were already there earlier that day for her. I still called for her. Her daughter one night came to my door and warned me that she had just been jumped earlier that day and the attackers knew where she lived.

The overall experience here has been a nightmare. Even though some of my experience was out of the managements hands. We will not be renewing our contract and we hope you think twice before you sign a contract here. I feel like I am living in the ghetto, which should not be the case.<//review>

<text>Long story short, the experience living here here for 3 years was roller coaster. The first year was amazing. Amazing monthly rate and hands-off management. The last two years were rough. The new management that took over made attempts to make changes to the apartment complex that just didn't work.

Rent was increased at the full 10% rate each year and they even force you to pay $75 a month for a washer and dryer. Keep in mind, this is not an option. You must pay for this washer and dryer. They couldnt care less when we mentioned that they weren't accounting for the extra cost for operation of the washer and dryer units such as water and electricity.

When we submitted our 60-day notice to vacate we were given two days for inspections of our apartment. The managment didn't come to either the preinspection (we called the office several times and I emailed the community manager who responded back via email and said everyone was busy with an issue with one of the other apartments. I emailed back and asked if all the office personnel was busy as well. I didn't understand why we didn't even receive a call or notification that our appointment was cancelled. The community manager didn't respond to the e-mail. I can furnish these e-mails upon request). Our final inspection which was supposed to be on November 14 also never happened. I tookm the day off work to be home for it and no one came. We also called the office several times and received no call backs. I guess my secret deposit will cover any cleaning needs for thr apartment but knowing exactly what that money is going towards would have been nice considering when we moved in nothing was new (carpet, appliances, laminate flooring, etc.).

There were many other issues but it's pointless to mention anything else. Living at Parcwood for more than a few years won't be feasible for most people considering the insane rent hikes but if you can afford it and you're not concerned with management that isn't transparent and does little to increase current tenants happiness (only concerned with bringing in news tenants are the much increased rental rates) then thus place may be for you and your family. Please keep in mind that the rent  increases are a serious concern. When we moved in 3 years ago the starting rent was $1760. If you simply look at the Parcwood website you'll see that 3 bedroom units start at $2273 now, only 3 years late. $500 more for the starting rent for an apartment seems a bit steep but I guess that's Southern California for you.

Please note, one of the employees at Parcwood named Val is awesome. She was always kind to my mother and she always cared. When the new management took over I believe Val was the only employee (or on a short list) who remained from the previous office personnel group. This may have been the wisest decision the new manament group made because she really is a pleasure to communicate with. Thank you again Val for always being so kind and professional and making us feel like you really cared.</text>< Resp>

< review>
This will be a fairly long and completely honest review. When my husband and I first moved here in June 2017, everything was great. Apartments were affordable, parking was awesome, and customer service was great. Unfortunately, after we moved in, things went downhill. Parking especially got worse. You don't need a permit to park in open spots so people would park there for weeks without moving (even inoperable cars) and never got towed or received a warning. The privacy gates hardly ever worked, they were always open. Homeless were always going through the trash cans at all hours of the day. People do not pick up after their dogs or keep them on leashes. I had one dog off a leash come and try to bite mine while I was walking. The laundry facilities needed to be monitored more often. People would leave their clothes in the washers/dryers all day long when nothing else was available. Machines were also often broken. However, my main issue is when we decided to move out.
We moved out after 6 months for financial reasons. We got the bill and realized we were being charged for cleaning (fine), carpet (fine), and painting. They are charging us the full amount to repaint all the walls when we were there for 6 months?! Also, they tried to charge us painting for a 2 BEDROOM APARTMENT when we were living in a studio. Tried to solve the issue in their office with Val, who said we would have to call the next day to speak to a manager. After I kept calling and emailing to get this issue resolved, they STILL have not resolved our move out invoice. They keep giving me excuse after excuse. So to say the least, their customer service is terrible, especially when you move out. DO NOT move here.< /review>

< text>
We have been here for almost 2 years and it's a nice community. The apartments are spacious and ours was one of the first renovated  prior to us moving in. It's very quiet here, people for the most part pick up after their animals, and the staff has been helpful. A few suggestions,  add more outing mail slots, we have to walk to another mailbox area there does not seem to be enough on property. Adding recycling would be a bonus,  I throw a lot of stuff out that should be recycled. I have never plugged a toilet more in my life then I do here. The system maybe sluggish, more then half the time I'm plugging just the water. The AC works well, but forget about programming it, it has a mind of its own. We have to continually monitor it. I'm not a fan of paying as much as we do for water, trash, and sewage usually it's between $89-101 a month. I feel like for a one bedroom apartment it's a lot. If the 3 bedroom apartments pay the same, I'm definitely paying to much. The pool is nice, been a few times very relaxing. The laundry room is good, but the dryers are not the best for things like bedding and towel. We usually have to double dry. The apartment complex WAY OVER WATERS! We have made numerous reports to the office with broken sprinkler heads and excessive amounts of mug from over watering. Now, if we pay for water and that's including outside and it's too much, please listen to your tenants. It's extremely wasteful. Parking for the most part is okay. Over all it is a nice place to live, easy access to freeways, I like the hardwood floors (vinyl) great for pets and durable, walls are a little thin but neighbors seems conscious of this, stores close by, and it's comfortable here. Overall even with its hiccups we would renew our least again. Unfortunately, they are raising rent prices, normal with almost all apartments I know. However our first hike was only $45 and our second hike this time is $85! They have almost doubled from the last time we renewed our least. Not thrilled about that, I'm assuming since after all the renovation of the other apartments they are trying to get old tenants to where new tenants are and to help with the cost of renovating. I saw on the website a one bedroom is going for $1377-$1400 something. I honestly would not pay over $1400 for this apartment. If they keep hiking the rates we will not be renewing. Because am I paying more for the same stuff I came on the least with that is not any different? What I feel like I'm paying for is a renovation that I have already been paying for. Not to mention it seems like tents move in and move out a lot. But, in fairness I don't know all their reasons. From our past neighbors it was due to rent hikes. Again nice community, but some things can definitely be improved.<//text>

<Text>This is a nice place to live but you will hate the front office staff and their un-professionalism. They will question if you even live on the premises then check the lease to make sure you're on it before giving you the key. They dont check this thoroughly if I'm on the lease when they are taking my rent check each month. The customer service is ridiculous here and I will definitely be writing the corporate office to inform them of every incident thus far.

**Addendum** I am upgrading my rating from a 1 to 3 stars. Since my last review, management seems to stay out of our apartment for "inspections" a lot more than before. We don't get as many notices informing us they need to enter in the middle of the day. Although I do find myself avoiding the front office as much as possible, they do seem a lot friendlier than a year ago. < review>
Yes, it is true. the staff is horrible. it is almost a sense of entitlement or that paid renters should be thankful to them. I lived there from 2014 to 2016. First, I was told that water & gas would be paid for during my tour. Nope, not true. They use this 3rd-party billing group that takes a cut every time. As a single individual I felt I was subsidizing other renters with more inhabitants. I was paying $30+/mo for sewage alone!  I called the 3rd-party billing group & they laughed at me & said I had no choice in the matter. The total additional bill came out to $80/mo & of course I had to pay separately for electricity. The first year, A/C broke down so often I had to contact the building owners' office for assistance.  It took a HUGE effort for them to replace the A/C. (when I left, I discovered I was living in an older unit that needed to be upgraded...but no excuse for poor response of fixing the A/C which honestly, the repair person told me it was a management decision to have him fill up the A/C gas every time for a quick fix rather than a permanent fix) There are good things about the place.  It is the best complex in the block. What made it distasteful was the staff and the padded costs via the 3rd-party billing; I had staff try to get away with additional charges when I left giving the appearance they were taking a cut of the vendor fees.< /review>

<user_id>117597402462417147483</user_id><time>1592587086499<//time><name>Carla Louise Design</name><gmap_id>0x80857d1422ef9649:0x2b8f251db777f4b6< /gmap_id></record>

<rate>5</rate><Review>Finally: high-quality, comfortable socks that ACTUALLY LAST!

The brilliant match/mismatch concept and great color/pattern selection makes it great for casual and semi-formal settings.

I waited for two years after getting my first pair (I have 8 pairs now) to write my review - because my biggest problem with socks is that they just don't hold up over time. Problems that I always run into with other socks:

1. The top part of the sock loses elasticity. Then they droop. Ugh.
2. The sock heel loses grip on your heel and scrunches up inside the shoe, extremely uncomfortable.
3. Fraying and unraveling of threads inside and outside of the socks.

However, the UR socks has held up extremely well, and surprisingly displayed none of the issues I listed above.  I've taken them for a beating too; I've worn them in everyday casual shoes (Converse All Star), leather boots, hiking boots, and even snowboard boots!

Oh another thing is these don't have giant uncomfortable seams in the inside of the toe part, even though these are reasonably thick socks, so you don't feel like there always a little pebble somewhere you can't get rid of above the toes.

The most comfortable and well-held up socks I've owned. Plus I get compliments with these wherever I go!

My favorite designs are the desert and cactus one and the camel/boat one.<//Review><Name>Frank Lin<//Name>< gmapID>

Material: 5/5
We got the "Dancing in Buenos Aires " and it's absolutely game changer! We like the materials because it keeps your feet dry all day long no matter how long you walk. (we did a 15 mile walk while traveling and it was perfectly fine!)

Design: 5/5
We like the ideas of having not-pairing pairing socks. One of the good things about these socks is that it comes with 2 different pairs in a similar color. It gives you more options to pair your socks in your own ways. (I personally like pairing them based on my mood, and they look interestingly match in a nice way.) We keep having compliment from families, friends, and even strangers and they all asked where the socks are from. (A compliment can count more from a stranger. You know that! )

These experiences definitely make us feel like we are getting more than we invested. Picking (designing) your own socks in the morning, and receiving compliment from stranger is a great way to start off a day. Sometime, we also find it's a great way to start off a conversation too as people always start it by asking us where did we get the socks. hahaha

Don't miss out. It's worth it!<//Text>

<rate>5< /rate><text>After 17 years of wanting a tattoo, I finally got one. Although it's super small, I love it.

My friend and I have talked about getting one together for a while. She has quite a few. We decided one Saturday night before we were going out that this was the night. I looked online and found a few places that were open past 8pm. Player's Ink had great reviews, was open later and close by. I called and they said AJ would be bale to take us if we could make it in before 9pm. We got ready and headed over.

< userid>
117268654829029824625< /userid>
<user_name>Natalia Chodelski<//user_name>< Time>
1507262428847<//Time>
<Rate>3< /Rate><Review>This review is for a piercing experience at Players Ink.

TL,DR: My piercings generally went well, but one was done with too small jewellery and it caused me problems and I had to go back and get it tapered up a size 2 days later. Now everything is good.  So I would reccomend Players Ink if you do your own research on the correct jewellery sizes and techniques for the piercing you want, and can be an informed and assertive customer.  However, if you want high quality internally threaded jewellery and the best sanitation and expert piercing possible, I would go to a specialty piercing shop.

I got 3 piercings done 3 weeks ago by Adrien. My experince was mostly positive and the piercings are healing up pretty well. However, some things from during and after my visit would make me hesitate to reccomend this place for complex or sensitive piercings. I think it is probably fine to get more common piercings like lobes/basic cartilage/lip/nose if you are comfortable doing your own research and know how to practice good aftercare.

Pros:
- My piercer, Adrian, and the staff were professional and kind.
- The piercing room was clean and organized.
- Adrian did a great job keeping everything clean and sanitary. skin cleaned with betadine, used new sterile needles and multiple pairs of latex gloves.
- They use the correct piercing techniques for the piercings which i got (i had researched beforehand and asked about the methods before committing)
- I had no signs of infection after (I also did 2x daily sea salt soaks, the standard aftercare to keep fresh piercings clean and help healing)
- i was a walk-in about 6pm on Saturday evening and it was not busy and i was seen quickly.
- The price was quite reasonable - though to some extent i now feel 'you get what you pay for' was true based on this experience vs a specialty piercing store like Cold Steel in SF.

Cons:
- Jewellery was disinfected in a cup in rubbing alcohol after I chose it - not with an autoclave. The other supplies were all sterile one time use.
- They only had externally threaded stainless steel jewellery - no titanium or internally threaded options.
- No paper of aftercare instructions given - so make sure you do your research and practice good aftercare to prevent your new piercing getting infected (2x daily sea salt soaks with 1/4 tsp salt per 8 oz boiled water).
- Unfortunately, one of my piercings, which was in a very sensitive area, was done with too narrow a gauge of jewellery (16g). This size is risky as it increases the chance of tearing the skin if the jewerly gets caught. It was also very 'sharp' feeling.

I ended up with too short jewerly in this latter piercing because while i initially asked for a 14g barbell, Adrien pressured me into 16g. His reasons seemed logical at the time, but it turned out he was incorrect, when I did my own research later.

Unfortunately, the smaller gauge did not work for me, it was quite painful and irritating.  I actually went back 2 days later and had the fresh piercing tapered from 16g to 14g and a bigger barbell inserted. This hurt, of course, but it was way better than risking the cheese wire effect from the thin jewelry on a very sensitive part of my body. The piercing was immediately much more comfortable, even an hour after sizing up the jewellery, and is healing well now.  The fact that Adrian was misinformed on how to do this piercing means I would definitely not recommend going there for something unusual or really complex - i would reccomend going to a specialty piercing shop for those.< /Review><Pics>None<//Pics><Resp>None</Resp>< gmap_id>
0x808fcca8f5bea0a5:0xd20e41c87062bb09</gmap_id>

<UserId.>118115514998790096976<//UserId.><Resp>None</Resp>< review>
Went to lunch with my co-workers. This is more of a restaurant then the normal Nordstrom cafe. So it's a sit and order not a order then sit place. I checked Yelp to see what you order and it said the crab bisque was really popular so I ordered a cup of that and the kale manchego salad. The soup was delicious. It tasted like a grilled cheese sandwich and tomato soup with bits of crab. It came with a small toasted cheese bread which was yummy as well. The kale salad was well seasoned and it had dried strawberries which was really unique. Overall I had a good experience although prices are more on the steep end.< /review>

<Text>Couple of friends and I came here on Christmas Eve Eve. The ambiance was fantastic. However, the entree (shrimp and asparagus risotto) I ordered didn't impress my taste buds. The shrimp and parts of the asparagus were slightly burnt/charred, but not quite bad enough to send back. The risotto itself was dry and lacked flavor. It came with 1 lemon wedge, I actually asked for more lemons to enhance it.

I had a bite of creme brulee and it was cold (perhaps it came straight from the fridge). My understanding of creme brulee is that it's hot/warm. Maybe I'm wrong. I will give them some credit of using real vanilla bean as little pieces of it showed up at the bottom of the plate.

The saving grace of this experience was the great service. Our waiter came by a couple of times and wasn't pushy. I was also in great company. The ambiance was also great in terms of the ability to have a conversation without shouting. All the tables are spread out enough for privacy. Located on the 2nd floor of Nordstrom. I'm willing to give this place another chance in the future.< /Text><Pictures>None< /Pictures>< Resp>

< text>
Discovered Michal and her incredible Fire Glass Studio while visiting LA. The glass studio has everything one needs to complete a fused glass masterpiece. Numerous classes for all skill levels are offered. There's always an instructor nearby to assist and all fused glass materials, tools, molds and kilns are on site.
